[SIZE=5][B]ItemMagnet v1.2.2 — Proximity Lore[/B][/SIZE]

[CENTER][I]Optional ambient messages near coordinates · Config GUI support · Off by default[/I][/CENTER]

[HR]

[B]What is new[/B]

[LIST]
[*][B]Proximity lore[/B] — configure coordinate zones that send ambient chat messages when players hold an active magnet nearby. Great for quest hints, dungeon atmosphere, landmarks, or RPG flavor.
[*][B]Config GUI[/B] — new [B]Proximity Lore[/B] section in [CODE]/itemmagnet config[/CODE]: enable/disable, scan interval, cooldown, require-active-magnet, and a zone editor for world + coords + radius.
[*][B]Per-tier messages[/B] — optional [CODE]tier-messages[/CODE] overrides per zone (e.g. different whispers for each magnet tier).
[*][B]Backwards compatible[/B] — absent or [CODE]enabled: false[/CODE] = zero behavior change from v1.2.1.
[/LIST]

[HR]

[B]Config example[/B]

[CODE]
proximity-lore:
  enabled: true
  scan-interval-ticks: 40
  require-active-magnet: true
  cooldown-seconds: 90
  zones:
    ancient_ruins:
      world: world
      x: 1200
      y: 64
      z: -800
      radius: 12
      messages:
        - "&8The resonator hums: &7The silence here is older than the village."
[/CODE]

Full reference: [URL='https://github.com/RMHavelaar101/item-magnet/blob/main/docs/proximity-lore.md']proximity-lore.md[/URL]

